## Introduction

RMS Titanic was a British ocean liner that sank on 15 April 1912 after striking an iceberg. It was on its maiden voyage from Southampton to New York City. The sinking resulted in the death of about 1,500 people, making it one of the deadliest maritime disasters in history. The Titanic carried some of the wealthiest people in the world, as well as hundreds of emigrants. The disaster spurred major changes in maritime safety regulations.

![Image of RMS Titanic](imgs/1469px-RMS_Titanic_3.jpg)

Source: [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Titanic)

---

# Why is the Titanic Famous?

The Titanic is notable for several reasons:

- **Largest ship of its time.**
- **Sank on her maiden voyage.**
- **Ignored multiple ice warnings.**
- **Insufficient lifeboats.**
- **Tragic loss of lives, including many prominent figures.**
- **Diverse stories of passengers and crew from various social strata.**

Source: [Encyclopedia Titanica](https://www.encyclopedia-titanica.org/titanic/)

